o fit in the qualitative trend of [Ca/H]61 in A-type stars, the\nwell-known feature of considerably weak Ca II K line in classical Am stars\nshould not necessarily be attributed to only this element diffusion scenario,\nfor which some unknown weakening mechanism specific to this resonance line may\nindependently be operative.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 30 Dec 2020 13:36:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-01-01"}
